		<td><b>Famicom to NES converter + CIC</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Does anyone know what kind of CIC circumvention these converters employ? I'm about to acquire one of <a href="http://famicomworld.com/system/converters/spica-t89-cartridge-converter/" class="postlink">these</a> and I don't want to risk damaging any of the hardware I'll be using with it, so I'd rather avoid any potentially hazardous CIC circumvention methods.<br /><br />Ideally, I'd like to mod the converter and install an actual CIC on it. Has anyone here ever attempted something like this? Does anyone have any advice for me before I go through with this? Thanks!

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
