	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Famicom to NES converter + CIC</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />From the article: &quot;Anyone whoâ€™s a collector of unlicensed games will be familiar with the way some of these things turn on: an eerie blank image followed by the startup screen.&quot;<br /><br />That sounds like Codemasters games, which use a charge pump to stun the CIC. Tengen games, which use a CIC clone, don't start this way. So playing King of Kings would produce stun pulses, whether it's Namco's version through the adapter or Wisdom Tree's version.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


